.\" Robin Wong and Erik Larson Fall 2013

.TH Format  "CSCI 241" "Oberlin College"

.SH FORMAT
.B FORMAT
-- a text formatting program

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sample_man
.B [
-h stuff
.B ]
.BR [ -q ]
.BR [ " -o output " ]
.BR [ "-r input" ]
<filenames>

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Does text formatting

.SH OPTIONS

.IP -w <int>
Changes line width to the next argument after the w flag.

.IP -r
Right-aligns the text

.IP -j
Fully justifies the text so that there is text on both the beginning and end of the line

.IP -s
Removes excess paragraph breaks.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
If you have error messages that you generate or non-zero return values, explain them here.

.SS Subsection
Subsections usually just have the first letter capitalized

